Quote:  A large number of the terms gathered from the prison were to do with drugs and devices and ways of taking them... Some interesting ones include:.. <i>rub-a-dub</i> (used occasionally to refer to ascetic anhydride, an agent added to Class B drugs, for example, to turn them into Class A drugs, for example, heroin).
